laboratory_examinations.findings: WBC at that time was 9.2 (normal range unspecified).

Several calculi are identified within the lumen of the gallbladder, largest measuring 1.0 cm x 0.9 cm; 1.0 cm x 1.2 cm calculus impacted within gallbladder neck/cystic duct; mild generalized mural thickening of the gallbladder wall; small amount of pericholecystic fluid and stranding; CBD normal in caliber; no intraluminal filling defects in CBD; small amount of free fluid in perihepatic and perisplenic areas; heterogeneous enhancement within liver parenchyma on arterial phase imaging, resolving on portal venous phase; tiny cortical cyst in left kidney measuring 0.6 cm x 0.5 cm; right kidney normal; both adrenal glands normal.
NO POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES SEEN.  NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.
